import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Net Generation')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    sns.barplot(x="year", y="net_generation", hue="source", data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net generation by source?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1,1))
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xlabel('Source')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.set(font_scale=1.2)
    sns.heatmap(data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum'), cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt='.2f', annot_kws={"size": 14})
    plt.title('What is the total net generation by year and source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source', fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('Year', fontsize=14)
    return plt;
